quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,166,"And verily, we (angels), indeed are those who glorify (Allâh’s Praises i.e. perform prayers)."
  37,167,"And indeed they (Arab pagans) used to say:"
  37,168,""
  43,55,"So when they angered Us, We punished them, and drowned them all."
  43,56,"And We made them a precedent (as a lesson for those coming after them), and an example to later generations."
  43,57,"And when the son of Maryam (Mary) is quoted as an example [i.e. ‘Îsâ (Jesus) is worshipped like their idols], behold, your people cry aloud (laugh out at the example)."
  44,40,"Verily, the Day of Judgement (when Allâh will judge between the creatures) is the time appointed for all of them -"
  44,41,"The Day when a Maulâ (a near relative) cannot avail a Maulâ (a near relative) in aught, and no help can they receive,"
  44,42,"Except him on whom Allâh has Mercy. Verily, He is the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful."
  45,31,"But as for those who disbelieved (it will be said to them): "
  45,32,"And when it was said: "
  45,33,"And the evil of what they did will appear to them, and that which they used to mock at will completely encircle them."
  46,19,"And for all, there will be degrees according to that which they did, that He (Allâh) may recompense them in full for their deeds. And they will not be wronged."
  46,20,"On the Day when those who disbelieve (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) will be exposed to the Fire (it will be said): "
  46,21,"And remember (Hûd) the brother of ‘Âd, when he warned his people in Al-Ahqâf (the curved sand-hills in the southern part of Arabian Peninsula). And surely, there have passed away warners before him and after him (saying): "
  47,10,"Have they not travelled through the earth, and seen what was the end of those before them? Allâh destroyed them completely, and a similar (fate awaits) the disbelievers."
  47,11,"That is because Allâh is the Maulâ (Lord, Master, Helper, Protector, etc.) of those who believe, and the disbelievers have no Maulâ (lord, master, helper, protector, etc.)."
  47,12,"Certainly Allâh will admit those who believe (in the Oneness of Allâh - Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds, to Gardens under which rivers flow (Paradise); while those who disbelieve enjoy themselves and eat as cattle eat; and the Fire will be their abode."
  48,1,"Verily, We have given you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) a manifest victory."
  48,2,"That Allâh may forgive you your sins of the past and the future,{1} and complete His Favour on you, and guide you on the Straight Path,",footnotes:1:{48:2} Narrated Al-Mughîrah: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم used to offer night prayers till his feet became swollen. Somebody said to him, "Allah has forgiven you your sins of the past and the future." On that, He said, " Shouldn‘t I be a thankful slave of Allah?" (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.6, Hadîth No.360).
  48,3,"And that Allâh may help you with strong help."